# FitCore: shared Member + Trainer screens

The unified Flutter app (`apps/fitcore_member`) serves **both** Member and Trainer. **Do not** maintain parallel “member-only” vs “trainer-only” screen trees for the same feature.

## Rules

1. **One screen per feature surface**  
   Build **common** widgets under `lib/screens/`, `lib/features/`, or `lib/presentation/` that both roles use. Only **branch inside** the widget when behavior or copy differs (tabs, labels, empty states).

2. **Role comes from RBMS / state**  
   Use `ref.watch(appRoleProvider)` (or a single session/auth provider when wired) or pass an explicit `AppRole` / `bool isTrainer` **into** shared screens. Avoid `TrainerFooScreen` + `MemberFooScreen` duplicates unless the information architecture is genuinely different (not just wording).

3. **Navigation**  
   Shells (`MemberShell` vs `TrainerRoleShell`) may differ by role, but **child route bodies** should call into the **same** screen widgets where the UX overlaps (e.g. profile, notifications, shared settings).

4. **New work**  
   When adding a screen: default to **shared** + role flags. Split into a second file only if the product requires **fundamentally** different layouts or data models—and document why in a one-line comment.

## Anti-patterns

- Copy-pasting a whole screen to `trainer_*` / `member_*` with minor text changes.
- Hardcoding “trainer” routes to widgets that duplicate member UI.

## Good pattern

```dart
// Shared screen; role tweaks copy and actions only.
class WorkoutsHubScreen extends ConsumerWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context, WidgetRef ref) {
    final role = ref.watch(appRoleProvider);
    final isTrainer = role == AppRole.trainer;
    // ...
  }
}
```
